# Linting and code quality

- ESLint extends Next.js presets: see [eslint.config.mjs](mdc:eslint.config.mjs).
- Ignored build outputs: `.next/**`, `out/**`, `build/**`, and `next-env.d.ts` via `globalIgnores`.
- Use `npm run lint` (defined in [package.json](mdc:package.json)) before commits.
- Prefer accessible, semantic HTML; Core Web Vitals rules are enabled.
- Keep components small, typed, and free of unused props/vars.
